界面新闻。
Interface news.
界面新闻是中国具有影响力的原创财经新媒体，只服务于独立思考的人群。
Interface News is an original and influential new financial media in China, serving only the people who think independently.
当地时间2020年2月19日，美国纽约，纽交所内场景。
February 19, 2020 local time, New York, United States of America, the scene inside the New York.
图片来源：视觉中国记者：崔璞玉“ 美国疾病预防控制中心(CDC)免疫和呼吸疾病中心负责人南希·梅索尼娅表示，他们预计新冠肺炎疫情将持续扩散，并呼吁美国企业、学校和社区做好准备，应对可能爆发的疫情。
Source: China Visual Correspondent: Nancy Mesonia, director of the Centers for Immunization and Respiratory Disease at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention in the United States, said they expected the outbreak to continue to spread and called on businesses, schools and communities to prepare for a possible outbreak.
”美国疾病预防控制中心(CDC)周二警告称新冠肺炎疫情将持续扩散，呼吁企业、学校和社区做好准备，应对可能爆发的疫情。
The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention warned Tuesday that the outbreak of new crown pneumonia would continue to spread, and called on businesses, schools and communities to be prepared for a possible outbreak.
当天，美股再次遭到猛烈抛售，恐慌指数持续攀升，债券等安全资产受到追捧。
On the same day, U.S. stocks were again slammed, panic indices continued to climb, and safe assets such as bonds were sought after.
周二收盘，道琼斯指数下跌879.44点，或3.15%，报27081.36点，两日狂泻逾1900点；纳斯达克指数跌255.67点，或2.77%，报8965.61点；标普500指数跌97.68点，或3.03%，报3128.21点。
The Dow Jones Industrial Average closed Tuesday down 879.44 points, or 3.15%, at 27081.36, down more than 1,900 on the two days, Nasdaq was down 255.67 points, or 2.77%, at 896.61, and the S & P 500 was down 97.68 points, or 3.03%, at 3128.21.
基准10年期美债收益率跌2.5个基点至1.352%，一度触及1.307%的历史低位，债券价格与收益率成反比。
The benchmark 10-year yield fell 2.5 basis points to 1.352%, briefly hitting a record low of 1.307%, with bond prices inversely related to yields.
衡量市场恐慌程度的芝加哥期权交易所VIX指数(CBOE Volatility Index)则继续上涨至27.85，涨幅达11.27%，盘中一度突破30关口。
The Chicago Board Options Exchange's VBOE Volatility Index, a measure of market panic, continued to rise 11.27% to 27.85, surpassing the 30-point mark.
安本标准投资公司(Aberdeen Standard Investments)高级投资经理詹姆斯·艾希(James Athey)在接受《华尔街日报》采访时表示：“疫情对经济冲击的规模似乎正在全球范围内扩大，此前被情绪推动上涨的股市出现了裂痕。
James Athey, senior investment manager at Aberdeen Standard Investments, said in an interview with The Wall Street Journal: "The scale of the economic shock appears to be widening around the world, following a rift in an emotionally driven stock market.
”美国疾病预防控制中心(CDC)免疫和呼吸疾病中心负责人南希·梅索尼娅周二表示，新冠病毒很有可能在社区传播。
Nancy Mesonia, director of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention's Center for Immunization and Respiratory Diseases, said Tuesday that the new crown virus is likely to spread in the community.
“这只是时间早晚的问题。
"It's just a matter of time.
”她说，CDC正就此进行准备，并鼓励民众也开始制定应对计划。
The CDC is gearing up for this and encouraging people to start planning their own responses, she said.
CDC还警告称，未来几周，如果病毒开始在美国社区传播，卫生部将不得不采取学校停课、企业停工的措施。
The CDC also warned that the health ministry would have to suspend schools and businesses in the coming weeks if the virus began to spread in the U.S. community.
截至2月24日，美国已确诊53例新冠肺炎病例，其中36例为日本“钻石公主”号游轮上的撤侨人员，3例为中国武汉的撤侨人员，14例为美国本土发现的确诊病例。
As of February 24, 53 cases of new crown pneumonia had been confirmed in the United States, of which 36 were evacuated from the Princess Diamond cruise ship, three were evacuated from Wuhan, China, and 14 were confirmed cases found in the United States.
投资银行杰富瑞(Jefferies)的股票策略师西蒙·鲍威尔(Simon Powell)在接受美国全国广播公司财经频道CNBC采访时表示：“我们越来越觉得，考虑到进入北美的中国人、韩国人和意大利人人数，很难相信美国的确诊病例数有公布出来的这样低，美国社区大规模爆发疫情的可能性正在增加……如果管理不当，将给市场造成极大的波动。
Simon Powell, equity strategist at investment bank Jefferies, told NBC: "There is a growing sense that given the number of Chinese, Koreans and Italians entering North America, it is hard to believe that the number of confirmed cases in the US is as low as publicly announced.
”据《华尔街日报》报道，白宫已经向美国国会申请动用至少25亿美元资金来对抗疫情，其中包括新增拨款12.5亿美元，挪用原本用于对抗埃博拉病毒的5亿美元。
The White House has asked the U.S. Congress for at least $2.5 billion to fight the outbreak, including an additional $1.25 billion to divert $500 million from the fight against the virus, The Wall Street Journal reported.
这笔资金将被用来研发疫苗、购置防护装备等。
The money will be used to develop vaccines, purchase protective equipment, etc.
世界卫生组织(WHO)发布的疫情报告显示，截至欧洲中部时间2月24日10时，全球除中国外共有29个国家累计报告确诊病例2069例，死亡病例23例。
As of 1000 CET on February 24, 2,069 confirmed cases and 23 deaths had been reported in 29 countries outside China, according to a report released by the World Health Organisation.
WHO总干事谭德塞表示，尽管意大利、伊朗和韩国的新冠肺炎病例骤然增加，令人深感担忧，但疫情尚未构成“大流行病”。
WHO Director-General Theresa Tanner says while the sharp rise in new crown pneumonia in Italy, Iran and South Korea is cause for deep concern, the outbreak has yet to constitute a "pandemic."
欧洲主要股指周二收盘全线下跌，意大利富时MIB指数跌1.44%，法国CAC40指数收跌1.94%，德国DAX指数收跌1.88%，英国富时100指数跌1.94%。
Europe's main stock indexes closed down Tuesday across the board, Italy's FTSE-MIB index fell 1.44%, France's CAC40 fell 1.94%, Germany's DAX index closed down 1.88%, and the FTSE 100 index fell 1.94%.
国际油价继续下行。
International oil prices continued to fall.
周二收盘，美国西得克萨斯中质原油(WTI)4月期货下跌3%，报49.90美元/桶；布伦特原油4月期货下跌2.4%，报54.95美元/桶。
West Texas Intermediate futures ended Tuesday down 3% at $49.90 a barrel, while Brent crude fell 2.4% to $54.95 a barrel.
国际金价亦大幅走弱，市场获利回吐迹象明显。
International gold prices also weakened sharply, the market profit is clear signs of recovery.
周二收盘，纽约商品交易所黄金期货市场交投最活跃的4月黄金期价比前一交易日下跌26.6美元，收于每盎司1650美元，跌幅为1.59%。
The most active April gold session on the New York Mercantile Exchange closed Tuesday down $26.6, or 1.59%, from the previous session to $1,650 an ounce.
